.TH F00-HEAD 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-head \- output the first part of files (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-head
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print the first 10 lines of each FILE to standard output.
With more than one FILE, precede each with a header.
Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU head\-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-lines\fR=\fIN\fR
print the first N lines instead of the first 10
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-bytes\fR=\fIN\fR
print the first N bytes
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR, \fB\-\-silent\fR
never print headers giving file names
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
always print headers giving file names
.PP
See
.B f00\-head \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON summary when supported
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV summary when supported
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR head (1),
.BR f00\-tail (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
